c: 48
v: 11
t: "The nomadic Arabs, who stayed behind, will say to you ˹O Prophet˺, “We were preoccupied with our wealth and families, so ask for forgiveness for us.” They say with their tongues what is not in their hearts. Say, “Who then can stand between you and God in any way, if He intends harm or benefit for you? In fact, God is All-Aware of what you do"